response:
Yeah exactly. I kind of know why we do them, but I forgot what I do know. And whenever I try to think about it now it just makes my head hurt cause I can't remember. 
Right now we're starting with working on near and far sightedness, so moving back and forth between the two to retrain my eyes and brain how to do it. And we want my eyes to start working together or teaming to take information in. But right now just doing the far and near exercises since I'm not able to do the teaming exercises properly.
Yeah that's true, and I know that. It's in so many of the books I've read. And I used to live like that. But with this it's definitely better. I'm more at peace I guess with where I am and where I might get too. But I don't know how to fully accept that I might not get better, cause then I feel like I'm giving up or I might as well just lose hope. Not a rational response, but not really one we can control right now. I do have more control over things but it's days like Thursday where I just lose control of everything, I can't do anything at all that just make it worse. But it's an ongoing process and I took Thursday a lot better then I would have 2 months ago. So just have to slowly change. As much as I want to be fine with where I am mentally and be at peace it can't happen overnight.
